entries.femaleVariant: How are you?
Where are you?
What's going on at Arasaka?
Any idea what's going on at Arasaka?
Only what I can surmise from what I see on TV.
But the wider the smile, the bigger the lies.
Yorinobu and his puppets grin at the cameras and insist that everything is under control.
Where are you right now?
In the city – where else would I be?
That's hardly an answer.
It is better you do not know my precise location – in the event that they apprehend you.
But I must give Night City some credit. It is easy to go underground here...
Gee, thanks.
As long as you become used to insects, mildew and no running water.
Won't press you on details.
Wise choice.
You all right, Goro?
Yes. Why the sudden concern?
Just asking. Something wrong with that?
We have shared interests – you and I.
Uh, just asking? Does everything with you have to have an ulterior motive?
Have shared interests – you and I. Or have you forgotten?
I apologize, that came off wrong. I, em... I am simply not used to such questions.
Certainly not.
Good. 'Cause catching lead in Night City's easier than catching a cold – and I need you alive.
I am alive and well, as you can see. You should worry about yourself.
People like me – either we are doing well, or we are in a grave.
Parade – how's the prep going?
Nearly everything is ready. Now is the hardest part – waiting.
But we should not talk about it. Not on the phone. Someone may hear.
OK. New subject.
Sure you're not just paranoid?
Right. In other news…
Never pegged you as the paranoid type.
It is better to be paranoid and alive than an idiot and dead.
I talked to Hanako.
Spoke with her. Not in person, but we spoke. You know who I'm talking about.
Mhm. She contacted me, too.
We went, as you say, all-in. And it worked.
We'll never know for sure.
Where are you now?
Your hideout's been blown. Probably literally. Where are you now?
I am done with squats, V. That is the most I can say – you will have to be content.
Hard to believe, but it's true.
No way of knowin' for sure. All we have's her word.
Words are different in weight. This depends on who speaks them. I am certain that Hanako's words bear the weight of truth.
Hard to believe, but it's true.
I don't trust anyone who talks to me via proxy.
Hard for me to trust anyone who goes via proxies.
How's Oda doing?
How's Oda doing? Still on the mend?
Arasaka provided him with the best medical care, but I cannot guarantee it will be enough. Wounded pride heals slower than bones.
Talk to you later.
Talk to you later.
Be safe, V.
As I said.
She made you an offer.
We'll meet in person.
I gotta find Soulkiller.
You're well informed.
Seem to know everything already. I gotta keep talkin'?
I know only what Hanako-sama saw fit to tell me. That is not much.
So, please – continue.
Got a meet in person, soon.
Very good. It would be hard to find a better sign of her trust.
Not too helpful so far. Gotta find Soulkiller first, 'cause Hanako – and I quote – her hands are tied.
Gonna be there,  too?
Not at this time. Arasaka is still searching for me – we cannot risk it.
So it is time to begin the search?
Yep, like Soulkiller's just something I could go pick up in Kabuki.
entries.maleVariant: Yeah, like Soulkiller's just something I could go pick up in Kabuki.

entries.femaleVariant: I cannot help you. But I believe it is worth a try. Your life depends on it.
But... It is only a matter of time, V.
Anything else?
How's the prep going?
Don't remind me.
